        "text": "fervent mind",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "]) for saving the soul [spirit] of the sinner. These three expressions occur again, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Corinthians 7:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". A syntheton[37] is added to each of them: but here he deals with them more moderately, and for the sake of euphemism [end.] puts ",
